Dear all,

1) It is said that Rig Veda has 21 saakhas. Only one Saakha is left out. It
is Saakala Saakha.

2) Yajur Vedas has two saakhas. I) Sukla and II) Krishna. Sukla has 15
saakas. Only 2 are known - Kaanva and Maadhyaandina 

2.1) The Krishna has 94 saakhas. Only 2 are available - Taitreeya and
Maitraayaneeya.

3) Sama Veda had 1000 saakhas. Only 3 are available now - Talavakaara,
Raanaayaneeya and Kouthuma.

4) Atharva Veda had 50 saakhas. Only 1 is available now - Sownaka.


Please let me know if my understanding is correct ? 

What happened to the other missing saakhas ? Were these destroyed by Muslims
rulers or British emperors ? Or people just could not remember it ?

Thanks for your help.




